# Intuition
- The Trees can have root nodes from 1 to n
- Left Subtree will have elements less than the root node
- Right Subtree will have elements greater than the root node
- Each left and right subtree can be treated as an individual tree which can have previousRoot-1 (starting from prevousRoot-1 till the left bound) number of root nodes and n-prevRoot (starting from previousRoot+1 till right end) number of root nodes respectively 

# Approach
- Base Case 1: For invalid boundary an empty tree can be created which is returned
- Base Case 2: When there is only a single node left the left and right value will be equal the value is pushed in the result as a node an returned
- For Every Tree/Subtree fix 1 node as the root node (i) and find all possible left and right Subtrees for that node.
- Every left Subtree can be combined with each of the right Subtrees to give a unique tree and vice versa
- Generate all possible combinations for the root node and push the root node in the result vector.

# Code
```
class Solution {
private:
    vector<TreeNode*> f(int left,int right){

        vector<TreeNode*> res;

        //Base case 1:
        if(left>right){
            res.push_back(NULL);
            return res;
        }
        //Base case 2:
        if(left==right){
            TreeNode* node= new TreeNode(left);
            res.push_back(node);
            return res;
        }

        //Fix the root node in i
        for(int i=left; i<=right; i++){
        //The left subtree will have elements from the left bound till i-1
            vector<TreeNode*> leftSubtree=f(left,i-1);
        //The right subtree will have elements from i+1 till the right bound
            vector<TreeNode*> rightSubtree=f(i+1,right);
        //Add all possibilities of the combinations of the left subtrees and the right subtrees for the root node i
            for(int j=0; j<leftSubtree.size(); j++){
                for(int k=0; k<rightSubtree.size(); k++){
                    TreeNode* node=new TreeNode(i);
                    node->left=leftSubtree[j];
                    node->right=rightSubtree[k];
                    res.push_back(node);
                }
            }

        }
        return res;
    }
public:
    vector<TreeNode*> generateTrees(int n) {
        return f(1,n);
    }
};
```

