**Approach**: Here we are always diving array elements in 2 parts, 'left' and 'right'. They both are heaps
'left' is max heap which will store the first half of small value of the total nums
'right' is min heap which will store second half of large value of the total nums

**Inserting a new num:**
Whenever we are inserting a number we will check if it will go in the 'left' or the 'right' part. 
If the value is smaller than or equal to the maximum value of the 'left' part then it will go in the 'left' part
If the value is greater than or equal to the minimum value of the 'right' part then it will go in the 'right' part
We will take care of some more conditions in the insertion process so that the difference of elements in both parts doesn't exceed by 1. See the comments in 'addNum' function.

**Finding median:**
If any of the heap is having more elements, (this difference will not be greater than 1) then its top value will be the median
Otherwise average of top values from both the heaps will be the median

