solutions.content:
Came up by myself before seeing any discussion solution.
The key idea here is to record ```count``` of each character at every position, and record the index of each occurrence of a character.
There will be two passes. The first pass is to calculate the ```count``` array and ```idxs``` array. The second pass is ```divide and conquer``` call. Each index will be examined at most once. Therefore O(n) in total.
```
class Solution {
    private int result = 0;

    public int longestSubstring(String s, int k) {
        if (s == null || k <= 0 || s.length() < k) return result;

        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
        int n = arr.length;
        // count[char][i] is the count of char before index i (exclusive) in arr
        int[][] count = new int[26][n + 1];
        // idxs[char][i] is the index of char's i-th occurrence in arr
        int[][] idxs = new int[26][n + 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 26; j++) count[j][i + 1] = count[j][i];
            int c = arr[i] - 'a';
            count[c][i + 1]++;
            idxs[c][count[c][i + 1]] = i;
        }

        divideNconquer(0, n, k, count, idxs);
        return result;
    }
    // test range [left, right)
    private void divideNconquer(int left, int right, int k, int[][] count, int[][] idxs) {
        if (right - left <= result) return;

        int invalid = invalidChar(left, right, k, count);

        if (invalid < 0) {
		    // it's valid, we update the result
            result = right - left;
            return;
        }
        // it's invalid; we discard this character.
        // we can test every range between this character's occurrences;
		// for example, if the invalid char is 'a', and the original range looks like: {...... a ... a ........... a ...}
		// Then every consecutive dotted range above will be tested in the next recursion call.
        int leftOccurrenceCt = count[invalid][left] + 1;
        int rightOccurrenceCt = count[invalid][right];
        while (leftOccurrenceCt <= rightOccurrenceCt) {
            int end = idxs[invalid][leftOccurrenceCt];
            divideNconquer(left, end, k, count, idxs);
            left = end + 1;
            leftOccurrenceCt = count[invalid][left] + 1;
        }
        // the last range
        divideNconquer(idxs[invalid][rightOccurrenceCt] + 1, right, k, count, idxs);
    }


    // if it returns -1, it means the range is valid;
    // otherwise, it returns a char that's invalid;
    private int invalidChar(int left, int right, int k, int[][] count) {
        for (int c = 0; c < 26; c++) {
            int occurrence = count[c][right] - count[c][left];
            if (occurrence > 0 && occurrence < k) return c;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

