solutions.content:
IDEA :

consider a substring from i to j, observation  that can be made :-
1. Every character occurring in substring must be occuring greater than or equal to k times.
2. Which means no character should occur  less than k times.
3. Which means  if  we encounter a character at position "m" (i<=m<=j)  which is occuring less than k times in that particular substring ( from i to j ), then that m should not be included in the answer substring or the part of substring from **i to m-1** will no longer extend its length i.e the substring has now been cut into two parts from **i to m-1** and **m+1 to j**.
4. if every character in substring is occuring greater than or equal to k times then the answer would be **j-i+1**.


This forms the basis of recursive solution.
```
recursive( i , j ) {
		1. store frequency of all chars at a place of the  substring from i to j
		2.loop from i to j 
			2.1 if any character found at index "m" having frequency less than or equal to k ( fetched from step 1 ) then call the recursive function from  i to m-1 and m+1 to j , and return the maximum from both the recursive solution.
		3. if you reach here that means every character in the substring is having frequencey greater than or equal to k so in that case return j-i+1 ;
}
```
CODE :

```
class Solution {
public:
    int longestSubstring(string s, int k) {
		// driver code
         int n =  s.size() ;
        return solve(0,n-1,s,k) ;
    }

	// main util function

    int solve( int i, int j, string s, int k){
        // base case,  easy to guess! 
         if(k==1) return j-i+1 ;
         if(i>=j) return 0 ;

        // step 1 , the place to store frequency , one can use maps too!
        vector<int> al(26,0) ;

        for( int m = i; m<=j ; m++){
             al[s[m]-'a']++ ;
        };

            // step 2 
        for( int m = i; m<=j ; m++){
			//step 2.1
             if(al[s[m]-'a'] < k){
                return max( solve(i, m-1,s,k), solve(m+1,j,s,k)); 
             }
        };

		// step 3 
		// if you reach here that means the  subtring has all characters having frequency greater than or equal to k 
         return j-i+1 ;
    }

