Explanation-
1. Let's try to calculate answer for each index i, such that index i is included in the string, if s[i, s.length()) is valid(every letter in that string has frequency greater than K), then that is the best you can get for index i.
2. If s[i, s.length()) is not valid, then we need to remove letters whose frequency is less than k till we get a string which is valid.
3. Let's calculate index[i][j], which is the minimum index of character j in the substring s(i, s.length()). 
4. Now if at s[i, s.length()) we have some pairs of characters whose frequency is less than k, then we will need to discard all of them and consider the new string s[i, ind].
4.  We will repeat the step 3 for each index i, till s[i, j] is valid and the length of our final string would be our answer for index i.
4. Take the maximum of the answer from each index i.

Complexities-
Time Complexity-O(26n)  This might feel a bit intuitive but at each index i, our while loop won't run more than 26 times.
Space Complexity-O(26n)

```
class Solution {
    public int longestSubstring(String s, int k) {
        //suffix sum of all characters. In other words, suffix[i] is the frequency of all the
        //letters in the s[i, s.length())
        int[][] suffix=new int[s.length()][26];
        for(int i=s.length()-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(i==s.length()-1){
                suffix[i][s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
                continue;
            }
            for(int j=0;j<26;j++){
                suffix[i][j]=suffix[i+1][j];
            }
            suffix[i][s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
        }
        //index[i][j]->minimum index where character j can be found in s[i,s.length())
        int[][] index=new int[s.length()][26];
        for(int i=s.length()-1;i>=0;i--){
            index[i][s.charAt(i)-'a']=i;
            if(i==s.length()-1){
                continue;
            }
            for(int j=0;j<26;j++){
                if(s.charAt(i)-'a'==j){
                    continue;
                }
                index[i][j]=index[i+1][j];
            }
        }
        int max=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            int ind=s.length();
            while(true){
                int temp=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                boolean fine=true;
                for(int j=0;j<26;j++){
                    if(suffix[i][j]-(ind==s.length()?0:suffix[ind][j])>0 && suffix[i][j]-(ind==s.length()?0:suffix[ind][j])<k){
                        temp=Math.min(temp, index[i][j]);
                        fine=false;
                    }
                }
                if(fine){
                    break;
                }
                ind=temp;
            }
            max=Math.max(max, ind-i);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```

