# Approach

Here i am calling function each time with some character in pass , and in that function i am excluding that character and checking for all subarrays , because that's how i am gonna get all possible subarrays . And we are also checking condition by iterating map while working on that function .

Now one question arises that what gonna happen if all characters of the string are satisfying  '>='
property , so for that i am again calling function with passing any other character that is not alphabet 
for example '#' . or we can add all charcaters of string s in map and call check function  .

# Complexity : O(N)
As 26 times i am calling function which is constant and complexity of function is O(N)

# Code
```
class Solution {

    bool check(map<char,int> mp,int k) {
        for(auto jj:mp) {
            if(jj.second<k) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true ;
    }

    int func(string s, int k,char c) {
        map<char,int> mp ;
        int i =0, j=0 , n = s.length() , ret = 0 ;

        while(i<n && j<n) {
            if(s[j]==c) {
                i = j+1 ;
                j++ ;
                mp.clear() ;
            }
            else {
                mp[s[j]]++;
                if(check(mp,k)) {
                    ret = max(ret,j-i+1) ;
                }
                j++ ;
            }
        }
        return ret ;
    }

public:
    int longestSubstring(string s, int k) {

        int i =0, j=0 , n = s.length() , ans=0;

        for(char it = 'a' ;it<='z';it++) {
            ans = max(ans,func(s,k,it)) ;
        }
        ans = max(ans,func(s,k,'#')) ;
        return ans ;
    }
};
```

