# Intuition
the intuition is to split the string into smaller parts whenever we find a char with freq less than k and recursively call the longestSubstring func for smaller parts of the string. keep track of the maximum size of valid string found so far. to check the freq of chars keep a freq array of size 26.

# Approach
1.check edge cases for when size of string is less than k and when k==1
2.keep two pointers start and end, iterate for end over the string
3.check freq of char, divide if needed and call the func recursively(pass the new string from start to (end-start))
4.update the start pointer to end+1
5.another edge case is the check for the last remaining part of string

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(nlogn)
O(n) as we are iterating over the whole string
O(logn) is the number of levels in recursion tree as we are dividing the string whenever needed
- Space complexity: O(n)
O(n) for recursion stack space 
O(1) for frequency array(independent of input size)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int longestSubstring(string s, int k) {
        if(s.size()<k) return 0;
        if(k==1) return s.size();
        vector<int> freq(26,0);
        for(auto it:s) freq[it-'a']++;
        bool valid=1;
        int maxi=0, i=0, j=0;
        for(j=0;j<s.size();j++){
            if(freq[s[j]-'a']<k){
                maxi=max(maxi, longestSubstring(s.substr(i,j-i),k));
                i=j+1;
                valid=0;
            }
        }
        if(valid) return s.size();
        //for remaining string
        maxi=max(maxi, longestSubstring(s.substr(i),k));
        return maxi;
    }
};
```

