Create a historgram of string. If all occurrences are >=k, return length of string.

Else there exists a bad character with occurence less than k. Remove the bad character and repeat the function call on all the resulting nonempty substrings, return the max function call on substrings.

Base case is when string is empty or is string has all character frequency >=k.

Runtime: O(26n)=O(n) because there are at most 26 characters, each recursion step removes a character, each set of subproblems has total length less than n.

Memory: O(1), recursion depth is 26, each step is fixed sized data structures of 26 characters.

```
class Solution:
    def longestSubstring(self, s: str, k: int) -> int:
        hist=collections.Counter(s)

        if not s or min(hist.values())>=k:
            return len(s)

        for key in hist:
            if hist[key]<k:
                bad_char=key

        substrings=s.split(bad_char)

        sub_problems=[self.longestSubstring(substring,k) for substring in substrings]

        return max(sub_problems)
```

