Hi there ! 

Idea : on each iteration we want to do the following 
1. check if at  current second ```timeSeries[i]``` is poisoned and for how long to compare it with next value to
2. indentify the actuall time Ashe was poisoned between two points ```timeSeries[i] ``` and ```timeSeries[i + 1]```
``` if(timeSeries[i] + duration > timeSeries[i + 1])``` 
it's either the time difference between points ```timeSeries[i + 1] - timeSeries[i];``` example[1,2]
or ```duration``` example [1,4];

```
class Solution {
    public int findPoisonedDuration(int[] timeSeries, int duration) {
        int result = 0; //number of seconds Ashe was poisoned.
        for(int i = 0; i < timeSeries.length - 1; i++){
            if(timeSeries[i] + duration > timeSeries[i + 1]) // checking how long poison will last.
                result+= timeSeries[i + 1] - timeSeries[i];  
            else
                result+= duration; // add duration if current time + duration is less than time when Teemo will poison Ashe again
        } 
        return result + duration; // add last one cause its missing :) 
    }
}
```
