solutions.content:
We know that the given Timeseries is already sorted so we can have 
only 2 cases to calculate the total time duration for which the Ashe will be in 
poisnous condition for starting n-1 timeSeries values.

**Case 1: when the Teemo timing of attack is clashing with next
time of attack**

**Case 2: when the Temmo timing of attack is not clashing with 
next time of attack**


Hence by this for case 1, we will just the calculate the total time by
counting the time from current attack to next attack by difference
between the two and substracting 1 from it (as the starting time is
included in counted time)

where as for Case 2, we will just add the duration in the time calculation 

and eventually for the last time in the timeSeries we will just add the
duration the total time calculated till now as it it the last time and no 
time will clash with the current last time.

Here is the Code of above approach:

```
class Solution {
public:
    int findPoisonedDuration(vector<int>& ts, int duration) {
        if(ts.size()==0) return 0;
        int ans=0,i=0;
        for(i=0;i<ts.size()-1;i++)
            if( ((duration+ts[i])-1) >= timeSeries[i+1] ) ans+=ts[i+1]-ts[i];
            else  ans+=duration;
        return ans+duration;
    }
};
```


